250 g Ground Beef
400 g Yellow Potato
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
7 g Dill
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
1 unit(s) Lemon
4 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
56 g Baby Spinach
2 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.38 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Remove brown spots from potatoes, then cut into 1/2-inch wedges.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1 tbsp oil. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast on the middle rack of the oven for 24-28 min, stirring halfway through, until tender and golden. (NOTE: For 4 servings, roast on the bottom and middle racks of the oven, switching baking sheet positions halfway through.)

Thinly slice spinach.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add spinach to the dry pan. Cook, stirring often, until wilted.
Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to cool slightly.

Meanwhile, core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Half cucumber lengthwise, then cut into 1/2-inch half-moons.
Chop dill.
Zest and juice half the lemon. Cut remaining lemon into wedges.

To a medium bowl, add breadcrumbs, cooked spinach, feta, Zesty Garlic Blend, garlic, half the dill and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt. Season with pepper.
Add beef, then combine.
Form mixture into eight (16) 2-inch-wide patties.

Reheat the same pan (from step 2) over medium.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then patties. (NOTE: For 4 servings, cook patties in 2 batches, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.)
Pan-fry for 3-4 min per side, until cooked through.**
Transfer to a plate, then cover to keep warm.
Meanwhile, to another medium bowl, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lemon juice, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar.
Add peppers and cucumber. Season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

To large bowl, add roasted potatoes, garlic spread, lemon zest and remaining dill. Toss to coat.
Divide potatoes, salad and beef patties between plates.
Drizzle yogurt sauce over top.
Squeeze lemon wedges over top, if desired.